Key Match Events: Coby White threw down an emphatic slam over San Antonio Spurs superstar Victor Wembanyama to ice the game with 15 seconds left.
Zach LaVine led the way for Chicago, scoring 35 points with 10 rebounds and 8 assists.
Post-Match Reflections: LaVine was feeling jealous of White's highlight slam after the win, saying how they talked about wanting to attempt a dunk over Wembanyama.
Miscellaneous Highlights: After trailing by as much as 19 points, the Chicago Bulls stormed back to take down the San Antonio Spurs 114-110, moving to 17-19 on the season.
Others: Zach LaVine has now scored 30+ in four of his last five appearances, proving all the doubters wrong after a disappointing 2023-24 season.
Bulls guard Coby White also played a huge role in the comeback, scoring 23 points
